description:
[i]Promotion for the novel.[/i]

When I opened my eyes, I found my soul synced into the popular dating sim game, &lsquo;Midnight&rsquo;! And although I was clearly one of the female protagonists, I possessed the body of Evenes Harin, the saint who is treated like a trivial extra. What&rsquo;s worse is that I must pursue one of the five male love interests and see it through to a happy ending in order to complete the game. 

Having attended the triple combo of an all-girls middle school, high school, and university wasn&rsquo;t enough of a debuff, having unintentionally put up an iron defense, I&rsquo;ve been in &lsquo;forever alone&rsquo; mode for 25 years. On top of that, I&rsquo;ve possessed the Saint seldom played due to her atrociously difficult route! This life is screwed up, and I&rsquo;m sure of it.

&ldquo;The more you look at it, the more novel this situation is.&rdquo;
 &ldquo;...?&rdquo;
&ldquo;How would you feel about living here like this?&rdquo;

Boasting a 99.9999% probability of a bad ending: the obviously crazy Archmage.

&ldquo;Evenes Harin.&rdquo;
&ldquo;?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Now I&rsquo;m sure you serve the devil. Or are you really crazy?&rdquo;

The epitome of rudeness: the seriously narcissistic Crown Prince. 

&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve made up my mind.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Shut up.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll make you into my first doll.&rdquo;

Instead of wrinkles on his brain, it&rsquo;s full of blooming flowers: the yandere Merchant Union&rsquo;s director.

&ldquo;...&rdquo;
&ldquo;... Do you have something to say?&rdquo;
&ldquo;[i](shakes head)[/i]&rdquo;

At the level of a shadowy human, a man of few words: the underworld guild leader.

At the lowest level, the most ordinary one is the empire&rsquo;s youngest swordmaster: the knight commander...

&ldquo;Lady Saint.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yes.&rdquo;
&ldquo;When I&rsquo;m together with my Lady, my heart feels at ease.&rdquo;
&ldquo;... Ah.&rdquo;
 &ldquo;I feel like I am one with Lunium.&rdquo;

As you can see, he is a zealous follower of the Temple of Lunium.

&ldquo;Would you not like to visit our house?&rdquo;
 &ldquo;... Your house?&rdquo; 
&ldquo;There is something that I would like to show you. Only to you.&rdquo;

And even the duke&rsquo;s daughter, who can be called the true heroine, is acting like this.

... Will I really be able to complete this game without any problems?
